WEBVTT

1
00:00:11.761 --> 00:00:15.515
[solemn music playing]

2
00:00:19.060 --> 00:00:21.146
[reporter 1] Hulk Hogan.
who some consider to be

3
00:00:21.229 --> 00:00:23.690
the biggest wrestling star of all time.

4
00:00:23.773 --> 00:00:24.649
has died.

5
00:00:25.233 --> 00:00:27.777
[reporter 2] Terry Bollea.
better known as Hulk Hogan.

6
00:00:27.861 --> 00:00:32.032
died today after suffering cardiac arrest
at his home in Clearwater. Florida.

7
00:00:32.115 --> 00:00:36.286
[reporter 3] Hogan's manager tells us
that he passed away surrounded by family.

8
00:00:37.245 --> 00:00:39.205
[solemn music heightens]

9
00:00:39.289 --> 00:00:42.125
[reporter 4] His wild personality.
pumped up physique.

10
00:00:42.208 --> 00:00:43.501
and handlebar mustache

11
00:00:43.585 --> 00:00:46.171
made him the face
of professional wrestling.

12
00:00:46.755 --> 00:00:49.340
His legacy also comes with controversy.

13
00:00:49.424 --> 00:00:52.886
[man] This won't surprise you. but I used
to watch him every day after school.

14
00:00:52.969 --> 00:00:54.471
-[host] Like a lot of kids.
-[man] Yeah.

15
00:00:54.554 --> 00:00:56.556
[host] Unlike a lot of superheroes.
Superman. Batman.

16
00:00:56.639 --> 00:00:58.933
you couldn't touch them. he was tangible.

17
00:00:59.017 --> 00:01:00.518
-[man] Sure.
-[host] To a lot of people.

18
00:01:00.602 --> 00:01:03.772
[reporter 5] They're very sad to see
their legend. their childhood hero.

19
00:01:03.855 --> 00:01:06.941
gone in what seems like such a sudden way.

20
00:01:07.025 --> 00:01:08.401
[music fades]

21
00:01:09.652 --> 00:01:11.154
[grunting echoes]

22
00:01:14.407 --> 00:01:17.160
[grunting and exhaling]

23
00:01:17.744 --> 00:01:18.995
[Hogan grunts]

24
00:01:22.665 --> 00:01:23.958
[exhales]

25
00:01:26.461 --> 00:01:27.420
[puffs]

26
00:01:27.504 --> 00:01:31.132
[dramatic music builds]

27
00:01:31.216 --> 00:01:33.051
Oh. [grunts]

28
00:01:33.927 --> 00:01:36.179
That's the hardest part. standing up.

29
00:01:37.430 --> 00:01:39.808
Old people take a long time to get going.

30
00:01:40.350 --> 00:01:41.976
Whoo.

31
00:01:42.060 --> 00:01:43.895
[grunts]

32
00:01:45.021 --> 00:01:46.689
[continues grunting]

33
00:01:48.775 --> 00:01:52.445
When I was the world's champion.
I had this crazy gym.

34
00:01:52.529 --> 00:01:58.118
Over the years. we've kind of scaled down
to theâ€¦ to the Geritol equipment here.

35
00:01:58.201 --> 00:01:59.911
[chuckles]

36
00:02:01.246 --> 00:02:02.956
[grunts]

37
00:02:03.039 --> 00:02:04.791
[interviewer] Do you feel strong?

38
00:02:04.874 --> 00:02:07.168
I feel okay.
but it's a pain in the butt. you know.

39
00:02:07.252 --> 00:02:10.713
because I have my son take the tops
off water bottles all the time for me

40
00:02:10.797 --> 00:02:12.132
because I can't turn them.

41
00:02:12.799 --> 00:02:14.926
Kind of embarrassing in a little way.

42
00:02:15.009 --> 00:02:16.469
[chuckles]

43
00:02:16.553 --> 00:02:18.138
But it's all good. huh?

44
00:02:18.221 --> 00:02:20.223
-[Nick Hogan] Ain't that bad.
-Could be worse.

45
00:02:20.306 --> 00:02:22.851
-I don't know. It's part of the deal. man.
-[Nick] Yeah.

46
00:02:22.934 --> 00:02:24.269
-You know?
-[Nick] Keep you humble.

47
00:02:24.352 --> 00:02:26.980
It keeps me humble.
Keeps me very grateful.

48
00:02:27.063 --> 00:02:30.108
In my mind.
I still think I'm 35 or 40 years old.

49
00:02:30.191 --> 00:02:33.528
but as soon as I look in the mirror.
I go. "Who the hell's that?"

50
00:02:33.611 --> 00:02:34.863
[dumbbell lands on floor]

51
00:02:34.946 --> 00:02:39.576
Getting down here
is like the only real peace in my life.

52
00:02:41.578 --> 00:02:44.914
Once I'd get in that ring.
I wouldn't worry about kids. wives.

53
00:02:44.998 --> 00:02:49.335
bills. problems. legal. criminal.

54
00:02:49.419 --> 00:02:51.087
[chuckling] Any type of problems.

55
00:02:52.255 --> 00:02:53.840
[exhales. then grunts]

56
00:02:53.923 --> 00:02:55.258
But I don't have that anymore.

57
00:02:56.551 --> 00:02:59.387
In wrestling. you should be remembered
from the wars you've been in

58
00:02:59.470 --> 00:03:00.972
and everything you've done.

59
00:03:01.055 --> 00:03:02.557
[crowd cheering]

60
00:03:04.809 --> 00:03:08.855
And a lot of that's been taken away
in the last 20 years.

61
00:03:09.647 --> 00:03:12.233
[reporter 1] Was there
a sinister side to his success?

62
00:03:12.317 --> 00:03:14.861
[reporter 2] Today. the WWE announced
they were dropping Hogan.

63
00:03:14.944 --> 00:03:18.156
Hulk Hogan fired by the WWEâ€¦

64
00:03:18.239 --> 00:03:21.534
[man] I think he's a liar.
I think he's a coward.

65
00:03:21.618 --> 00:03:23.244
[interviewer]
There's certainly some things

66
00:03:23.328 --> 00:03:26.956
that you would want to be remembered for
more than others. right?

67
00:03:27.957 --> 00:03:29.334
[tape rewinding]

68
00:03:29.918 --> 00:03:31.085
Yeah.

69
00:03:31.169 --> 00:03:32.212
[exhales]

70
00:03:32.295 --> 00:03:33.296
Of course.

71
00:03:34.672 --> 00:03:38.885
["It's a Long Way to the Top"
by AC/DC playing]

72
00:03:39.886 --> 00:03:42.055
[Hogan] I think people
wanna know the truth.

73
00:03:42.138 --> 00:03:45.558
-Who was this guy. really?
-[Linda Hogan] Is Hulk in the building?

74
00:03:45.642 --> 00:03:47.644
Look what I'm married to.

75
00:03:48.311 --> 00:03:49.646
Yeah. yeah.

76
00:03:49.729 --> 00:03:52.315
I believe in what I'm doing.
and people get behind that.

77
00:03:52.398 --> 00:03:55.318
They get behind me.
They know I train. pray. eat my vitamins.

78
00:03:55.401 --> 00:03:57.862
If you say your prayers.
if you eat your vitamins. man.

79
00:03:57.946 --> 00:03:59.697
sooner or later. you get what you want.

80
00:03:59.781 --> 00:04:00.698
This is serious.

81
00:04:01.532 --> 00:04:03.034
Come on. Hulk!

82
00:04:04.035 --> 00:04:05.828
â™ª Ridin' down the highway â™ª

83
00:04:07.163 --> 00:04:08.706
â™ª Goin' to a show â™ª

84
00:04:08.790 --> 00:04:11.042
[announcer] Beach-boy blonde.
his body of bronze.

85
00:04:11.125 --> 00:04:14.003
standing 6'9". and weighing 345.

86
00:04:14.087 --> 00:04:15.755
His name is Hulk Hogan.

87
00:04:15.838 --> 00:04:18.216
[presenter] When you were born.
they didn't say.

88
00:04:18.299 --> 00:04:21.344
"This looks like a baby Hulk.
We'll name him Hulk Hogan."

89
00:04:21.427 --> 00:04:22.303
[both chuckling]

90
00:04:22.387 --> 00:04:24.472
No. but I grew into the name.
that's for sure.

91
00:04:25.014 --> 00:04:29.185
What you gonna do
when Hulkamania runs wild on you?

92
00:04:29.269 --> 00:04:32.897
â™ª It's a long way to the top
If you wanna rock 'n' rollâ€¦ â™ª

93
00:04:32.981 --> 00:04:35.566
[reporter 1] Today. he is
the biggest name in wrestling.

94
00:04:35.650 --> 00:04:38.403
â™ª It's a long way to the topâ€¦ â™ª

95
00:04:38.486 --> 00:04:42.156
[reporter 2] One of the most famous
athletes in the history of the world.

96
00:04:44.951 --> 00:04:47.328
Man. it feels great
to be on top of the mountain!

97
00:04:47.412 --> 00:04:50.415
It feels like I got
about a million volts of electricity

98
00:04:50.498 --> 00:04:52.500
running through these 24-inch pythons!

99
00:04:52.583 --> 00:04:53.876
[toy] Hulkster rules. brother.

100
00:04:53.960 --> 00:04:57.213
[reporter 3] A man who calls himself
the ultimate male.

101
00:04:57.297 --> 00:04:59.382
[reporter 4] The ultimate all-American.

102
00:04:59.465 --> 00:05:02.176
Here in America. you gotta work hard.
love hard. and die hard. man.

103
00:05:03.344 --> 00:05:05.096
â™ª Such a long way â™ª

104
00:05:05.179 --> 00:05:06.639
-[music ends]
-[clang echoes]

105
00:05:12.437 --> 00:05:14.981
[Hogan] I can't predict
and tell you right now

106
00:05:15.064 --> 00:05:17.108
what the final act
of the story is gonna be.

107
00:05:17.191 --> 00:05:21.696
[nostalgic music playing]

108
00:05:29.996 --> 00:05:33.291
I'm not looking for a legacy
pat on the back. for sure.

109
00:05:34.625 --> 00:05:36.794
Not everyone is going to love you.

110
00:05:39.339 --> 00:05:42.175
Some people hate me. butâ€¦

111
00:05:44.135 --> 00:05:46.637
I'm definitely the greatest wrestler
of all time.

112
00:05:46.721 --> 00:05:47.638
I'm Hulk Hogan.

113
00:05:47.722 --> 00:05:49.932
-Mr. Hulk Hogan!
-[crowd cheering]

114
00:05:50.016 --> 00:05:53.227
Here he is. Hulk Hogan!

115
00:05:53.311 --> 00:05:55.146
[presenter] The man
who needs no introduction.

116
00:05:55.229 --> 00:05:57.106
-Hogan!
-Would you welcome Hulk Hogan?

117
00:05:57.190 --> 00:05:59.192
[crowd cheering]

118
00:05:59.275 --> 00:06:00.735
I'm Hulk Hogan.

119
00:06:01.527 --> 00:06:04.322
[gentle music playing]

120
00:06:10.620 --> 00:06:14.540
Let's see if I can get through another day
and listen to myself talk.

121
00:06:14.624 --> 00:06:16.376
-Good grief.
-[interviewer chuckles]

122
00:06:16.459 --> 00:06:18.753
[Hogan] Moments away.
Makeup and hair. please.

123
00:06:18.836 --> 00:06:22.382
[imitates voice of female makeup artist]
"I'm here. I can do this."

124
00:06:22.465 --> 00:06:24.217
"Couple of frizzies here. Hulk."

125
00:06:24.300 --> 00:06:25.468
[as Hogan] "Thank you. dear."

126
00:06:25.551 --> 00:06:27.637
["Va. pensiero" from Nabucco
by Giuseppe Verdi playing]

127
00:06:27.720 --> 00:06:29.555
[reporter] Fans recognize
Hulk Hogan as a hero.

128
00:06:30.139 --> 00:06:31.516
[reporter 2] He's bigger than life.

129
00:06:31.599 --> 00:06:35.061
A real hero who gives his all
for all the right reasons.

130
00:06:35.645 --> 00:06:37.688
[interviewer]
Do you consider yourself a hero?

131
00:06:38.272 --> 00:06:41.234
[Hogan]
I don't consider myself a hero at all.

132
00:06:41.317 --> 00:06:45.988
But I'm very aware now.
after all these years.

133
00:06:46.072 --> 00:06:51.035
what that Hulk Hogan presence means.
um. you know. to the fans.

134
00:06:51.119 --> 00:06:52.954
[yelling excitedly]

135
00:06:53.037 --> 00:06:54.622
"I was not a mere mortal man."

136
00:06:54.705 --> 00:06:57.708
"I was the superhero Hulk Hogan."
when I had my stature.

137
00:06:57.792 --> 00:06:58.626
[yells]

138
00:06:58.709 --> 00:07:01.003
The Hulk Hogan character is over the top.

139
00:07:01.087 --> 00:07:02.630
It's a fake character.

140
00:07:02.713 --> 00:07:06.217
You know. hopefully people
can understand that someday.

141
00:07:06.300 --> 00:07:10.138
Man. I say my prayers. take my vitamins.
and everything I do is positive.

142
00:07:10.221 --> 00:07:14.142
But. yeah. it's two different people.
You know. it's like me playing Dracula.

143
00:07:14.225 --> 00:07:16.352
I don't come home
and bite my wife in the neck

144
00:07:16.436 --> 00:07:18.438
and suck the blood out of my kids' necks.

145
00:07:18.521 --> 00:07:21.065
But. duh. if you want
to believe that. go ahead.

146
00:07:21.149 --> 00:07:22.483
But when I come in the house.

147
00:07:22.567 --> 00:07:25.153
the headband comes off.
the bald head's there.

148
00:07:25.236 --> 00:07:27.447
and my wife calls me Terry.

149
00:07:28.364 --> 00:07:30.908
-[Linda] Terry! Why do you do that?
-Watch this.

150
00:07:30.992 --> 00:07:32.743
Terry won't leave this part out.

151
00:07:32.827 --> 00:07:36.664
We're going to take some movies of Terry.
and we're going to make a video.

152
00:07:37.165 --> 00:07:39.375
There were only a handful of people
knew him as Terry.

153
00:07:39.459 --> 00:07:41.627
I knew him deeply as himself.

154
00:07:41.711 --> 00:07:43.838
Oh my God. look at this.
We were always tan.

155
00:07:43.921 --> 00:07:45.673
I turned Terry on to a tanning bed.

156
00:07:45.756 --> 00:07:48.593
He didn't even know what they were.
and he had to stay tanned for work.

157
00:07:48.676 --> 00:07:50.595
Oop. Terry's naked.

158
00:07:50.678 --> 00:07:53.681
["Make Me Smile (Come Up and See Me)"
by Steve Harley & Cockney Rebel playing]

159
00:07:53.764 --> 00:07:56.476
â™ª You've broken every codeâ€¦ â™ª

160
00:07:56.559 --> 00:07:57.435
[cheering]

161
00:07:57.518 --> 00:08:01.981
[Linda] The fans just liked believing
that Hulk was like Superman.

162
00:08:02.064 --> 00:08:03.691
[commentator] Drop it out there! Oneâ€¦

163
00:08:04.484 --> 00:08:06.819
â™ª You spoiled the gameâ€¦ â™ª

164
00:08:06.903 --> 00:08:08.196
-Hey!
-[Linda] I know him.

165
00:08:08.279 --> 00:08:10.072
When you're with somebody that long.

166
00:08:10.156 --> 00:08:14.327
through thick and thin. good and bad.
tired. happy. sad. you know.

167
00:08:14.911 --> 00:08:16.704
you learn that person very well.

168
00:08:16.787 --> 00:08:19.749
â™ª Ooh. la-la-la â™ª

169
00:08:19.832 --> 00:08:22.543
And I was always the one with the camera.

170
00:08:22.627 --> 00:08:25.505
This is the. uh. greatest wall.

171
00:08:25.588 --> 00:08:27.840
because the greatest person
is on this wall.

172
00:08:27.924 --> 00:08:30.301
When I met Terry. I asked.
"Do you have family?"

173
00:08:30.384 --> 00:08:32.887
He laid out his situation.

174
00:08:32.970 --> 00:08:35.640
Let's show these people the refrigerator

175
00:08:35.723 --> 00:08:40.269
that took me from a mere 196 pounds
when I was 12 years old

176
00:08:40.353 --> 00:08:43.481
to a whopping 305-pound Hulk Hogan.

177
00:08:44.065 --> 00:08:46.734
I grew up in Florida. in South Tampa.

178
00:08:48.110 --> 00:08:50.696
We were broke. and I hated it.

179
00:08:50.780 --> 00:08:56.827
Especially watching how my dad slaved
in the sun as a construction worker.

180
00:08:56.911 --> 00:08:59.330
-These old broken steps. man.
-[Linda] Yeah.

181
00:08:59.413 --> 00:09:05.253
As a kid. I made a decision
that financially I'd never live like that.

182
00:09:05.336 --> 00:09:07.964
[Linda] We got Pete Bollea.

183
00:09:08.047 --> 00:09:10.758
[Hogan] My dad was that old.
hard-school Italian. you know.

184
00:09:11.592 --> 00:09:13.803
And he was a little rough on me.
that's for sure.

185
00:09:13.886 --> 00:09:16.931
They weren't the type of parents
that would tell you they love you.

186
00:09:17.014 --> 00:09:18.349
That would never happen.

187
00:09:18.432 --> 00:09:20.434
Terry was a mistake-type child.

188
00:09:21.018 --> 00:09:24.939
They had Allan.
and then eight years later. had Terry.

189
00:09:25.481 --> 00:09:28.693
My older brother. Allan.
he was the tough guy.

190
00:09:28.776 --> 00:09:30.152
Allan was my dad's favorite.

191
00:09:30.236 --> 00:09:32.280
He was always talking
about how strong he was.

192
00:09:32.363 --> 00:09:36.659
and he would just tell me. you know.
"You're not like your brother." you know?

193
00:09:36.742 --> 00:09:40.079
I didn't understand that
and always had a big chip on my shoulder.

194
00:09:41.038 --> 00:09:43.541
But. you know. I hated confrontations.

195
00:09:45.585 --> 00:09:47.878
[Linda] He wasn't
the loudmouth you see on TV.

196
00:09:47.962 --> 00:09:50.631
He was very soft-spoken. shy.

197
00:09:50.715 --> 00:09:53.009
No. I wasn't always this confident.

198
00:09:53.092 --> 00:09:55.011
[interviewer] When did that change?

199
00:09:55.094 --> 00:09:56.304
[upbeat music playing]

200
00:09:56.387 --> 00:09:57.471
[Hogan] On the weekends.

201
00:09:57.555 --> 00:10:01.142
Florida Championship Wrestling
would come on the TV back then.

202
00:10:01.225 --> 00:10:04.353
I'd never seen anything like that.

203
00:10:04.437 --> 00:10:07.440
["Over the Top"
by Graham Preskett playing]

204
00:10:07.523 --> 00:10:09.525
[commentator speaking indistinctly]

205
00:10:11.527 --> 00:10:13.279
I had no idea that this existed.

206
00:10:14.030 --> 00:10:18.075
I was probably 8 or 9 years old
when we first went in person.

207
00:10:18.159 --> 00:10:22.913
They had these great characters.
the conflict between good and bad.

208
00:10:22.997 --> 00:10:26.876
how into it the fans were.
they were loyal. dedicated fans.

209
00:10:26.959 --> 00:10:28.878
I love it! I love it!

210
00:10:28.961 --> 00:10:32.381
[Hogan] There was this love and energy
that they were all getting there.

211
00:10:32.465 --> 00:10:33.466
I could feel it. man.

212
00:10:34.050 --> 00:10:37.887
And the one guy that really hooked me
was "The American Dream." Dusty Rhodes.

213
00:10:37.970 --> 00:10:40.473
[announcer] Truly. the idol of the people.
"The American Dream."

214
00:10:40.556 --> 00:10:42.933
[Hogan] His whole rap reeled us in.

215
00:10:43.017 --> 00:10:46.270
The razzmatazz.
my new Flandango waltz hold.

216
00:10:46.354 --> 00:10:50.149
I'm so quick. I'm so fast.
Terry Funk is nothing but a punk.

217
00:10:50.733 --> 00:10:53.527
[Hogan] The energy
would just drag you up out of any hole.

218
00:10:53.611 --> 00:10:56.113
I went there all through childhood.

219
00:10:57.448 --> 00:10:58.491
I was hooked.

220
00:11:02.161 --> 00:11:03.954
That's what I wanted to do.

221
00:11:05.956 --> 00:11:07.708
I wanted to be a wrestler.

222
00:11:10.169 --> 00:11:11.420
[music ends]

223
00:11:11.504 --> 00:11:14.215
The problem was
I was scared to death of those guys.

224
00:11:14.298 --> 00:11:15.341
[growls]

225
00:11:15.424 --> 00:11:17.176
Most of them were 300 pounds and over.

226
00:11:17.259 --> 00:11:20.054
and they had teeth knocked out
and broken noses and cauliflower ears.

227
00:11:20.638 --> 00:11:22.640
It scared the bejesus out of me.

228
00:11:22.723 --> 00:11:26.477
I believed professional wrestling
was completely real.

229
00:11:27.978 --> 00:11:29.522
I knew I couldn't do it.

230
00:11:30.481 --> 00:11:31.524
I was real fat.

231
00:11:31.607 --> 00:11:35.027
Didn't take my shirt off. ever.
when I went to the beach

232
00:11:35.111 --> 00:11:36.237
because I needed a bra.

233
00:11:37.154 --> 00:11:42.159
Pretty much. I was living off. you know.
Burger King and Snickers bars.

234
00:11:43.285 --> 00:11:44.829
Played Little League baseball.

235
00:11:45.496 --> 00:11:49.375
But they could throw me out at second.
I was so fat and slow.

236
00:11:50.292 --> 00:11:51.502
So I got into bowling.

237
00:11:53.921 --> 00:11:58.884
But then my life changed when I realized
I could make money playing music.

238
00:11:58.968 --> 00:12:01.679
[rock music playing]

239
00:12:01.762 --> 00:12:04.432
[Linda] Terry was a talented bass player.

240
00:12:04.515 --> 00:12:07.685
He would have been Guns N' Roses.
like. he's that level.

241
00:12:09.812 --> 00:12:14.984
I learned that I liked being
in front of the crowd and being on stage.

242
00:12:15.067 --> 00:12:18.320
But my dad was upset
that I had quit school

243
00:12:18.404 --> 00:12:20.865
and was running around
in a rock and roll band

244
00:12:20.948 --> 00:12:23.367
and lifting weights like an idiot.

245
00:12:24.577 --> 00:12:27.872
It led to me. you know.
having a big blow out with my parents

246
00:12:27.955 --> 00:12:29.373
and getting kicked out of the house.

247
00:12:30.166 --> 00:12:31.751
â™ª You got it â™ª

248
00:12:32.376 --> 00:12:36.672
So. a few years after high school.
we had a little following in North Tampa.

249
00:12:36.756 --> 00:12:39.884
Then all of a sudden.
these wrestlers were coming in the bar.

250
00:12:39.967 --> 00:12:42.803
[gasps] Oh my gosh.
I'm on stage. and here's these guys.

251
00:12:42.887 --> 00:12:45.973
I'm scared to death of guys
like "Superstar" Billy Graham.

252
00:12:46.056 --> 00:12:48.058
You know what a fist sandwich is?

253
00:12:48.726 --> 00:12:50.102
[Hogan] And Brian Blair.

254
00:12:50.186 --> 00:12:54.940
My first memory of meeting Terry
was when he was playing bass guitar.

255
00:12:55.024 --> 00:12:56.442
and he'd stand out so much.

256
00:12:56.525 --> 00:12:59.153
He was in these platform heels
and had jewelry on.

257
00:12:59.236 --> 00:13:02.740
and long blonde hair. suntan. big muscles.

258
00:13:02.823 --> 00:13:04.325
I mean. he was the show.

259
00:13:04.408 --> 00:13:06.827
The music was good.
but he was. like. the show.

260
00:13:07.578 --> 00:13:10.790
What shocked me more than anything
was that they weren't mean to me.

261
00:13:10.873 --> 00:13:12.166
[chuckles]

262
00:13:12.792 --> 00:13:15.795
I didn't realize they were grooming me.

263
00:13:15.878 --> 00:13:18.047
[engine rumbling]

264
00:13:18.130 --> 00:13:21.509
And they took me to all the matches.
so I could get in free.

265
00:13:21.592 --> 00:13:23.511
[solemn music playing]

266
00:13:25.930 --> 00:13:30.726
And then one of the biggest nights
of my life changed everything.

267
00:13:32.228 --> 00:13:35.606
We saw Steve Keirn
at Fort Homer Hesterly Armory.

268
00:13:36.774 --> 00:13:42.822
The bad guy was just waylaying his ass.
and the referee told him to knock it off.

269
00:13:44.573 --> 00:13:45.616
"Let go of me. ref."

270
00:13:45.699 --> 00:13:48.410
I remember he looked right down
at Steve Keirn.

271
00:13:49.495 --> 00:13:50.538
I read his lips.

272
00:13:51.455 --> 00:13:53.249
He said. "Hit me. Hit me."

273
00:13:53.332 --> 00:13:54.875
I went. "What?"

274
00:13:54.959 --> 00:13:56.335
And Steve hit him.

275
00:13:56.919 --> 00:13:58.629
And he goes. "Again. again."

276
00:13:58.712 --> 00:14:02.258
And he made this comeback from underneath.
I was like. "What?!"

277
00:14:02.341 --> 00:14:04.093
I just didn't believe it.

278
00:14:05.052 --> 00:14:08.514
I was disillusioned for about two seconds.
and I got over it.

279
00:14:08.597 --> 00:14:10.850
All of a sudden. the door opens

280
00:14:10.933 --> 00:14:14.728
and I knew I didn't have to be a tough guy
to get in the business.

281
00:14:14.812 --> 00:14:18.399
[heroic music playing]

282
00:14:18.482 --> 00:14:21.443
[Blair] They don't want to tell you
that it's not real.

283
00:14:22.027 --> 00:14:23.863
They want you to believe that it is.

284
00:14:25.739 --> 00:14:30.411
But people don't realize
what your body goes through.

285
00:14:30.494 --> 00:14:33.789
You get your butt kicked
in professional wrestling.

286
00:14:38.002 --> 00:14:40.004
[music fades]

287
00:14:43.549 --> 00:14:44.550
Wow.

288
00:14:46.176 --> 00:14:48.012
I remember all too well.

289
00:14:48.762 --> 00:14:51.265
This is where
Terry and I learned to wrestle.

290
00:14:51.348 --> 00:14:53.100
It was called The Dungeon.

291
00:14:53.726 --> 00:14:55.477
["Showbiz Kid" by Sleaze playing]

292
00:14:55.561 --> 00:14:57.980
[Hogan]
I had made the decision to go for it.

293
00:14:59.648 --> 00:15:05.195
And I just believed that I knew exactly
what I had to do to run with the pack.

294
00:15:05.988 --> 00:15:08.032
[Blair] It was brutal. Brutal.

295
00:15:08.115 --> 00:15:10.284
What you had to go through
to get into the business.

296
00:15:11.076 --> 00:15:14.455
The newer guys. they have no clue.
They have no clue.

297
00:15:15.497 --> 00:15:17.791
[Hogan] I spent a year in the gym
training twice a day

298
00:15:17.875 --> 00:15:20.336
and laying in the sun all day long.

299
00:15:20.419 --> 00:15:24.590
And like a fool. I told everybody
I was going to be a wrestler.

300
00:15:24.673 --> 00:15:27.593
"I'm going to be a wrestler."
That's the wrong thing to do.

301
00:15:27.676 --> 00:15:30.137
One of the teachers
put his forearm in my shin

302
00:15:30.220 --> 00:15:32.056
and grabbed my toe. snap.

303
00:15:33.599 --> 00:15:36.310
And they broke his leg.
literally broke it.

304
00:15:37.853 --> 00:15:39.271
-[music ends]
-[bone cracks]

305
00:15:39.813 --> 00:15:42.274
I was living in a hotel room at the time.

306
00:15:42.358 --> 00:15:43.817
Umâ€¦

307
00:15:43.901 --> 00:15:47.613
I tried to come home whenever I could.
but I wasn't welcome there. you know.

308
00:15:47.696 --> 00:15:49.114
[speaking indistinctly]

309
00:15:49.198 --> 00:15:52.034
When my dad would go to work.
I'd run back to the house.

310
00:15:52.117 --> 00:15:53.160
Sweetheart.

311
00:15:53.243 --> 00:15:55.329
[Hogan] My mom would cook for me
and take care of me.

312
00:15:55.412 --> 00:15:57.373
Then I could sleep in his bed.

313
00:15:57.456 --> 00:16:00.709
"You gotta get outta here.
Your dad's coming home." So I'd take off.

314
00:16:01.543 --> 00:16:04.213
You know. my leg getting broke

315
00:16:04.296 --> 00:16:06.799
was minuscule
compared to what he put me through. so.

316
00:16:06.882 --> 00:16:08.717
Bang. bang. bang!

317
00:16:08.801 --> 00:16:11.887
I had to go back.
There was no quitting for me.

318
00:16:12.388 --> 00:16:13.847
[groans]

319
00:16:14.848 --> 00:16:17.810
As soon as I got better.
I started showing up down there.

320
00:16:17.893 --> 00:16:19.770
[intense music playing]

321
00:16:19.853 --> 00:16:21.939
[Linda] That made Terry
want to try even harder.

322
00:16:22.022 --> 00:16:23.774
Like. "You're not gonna keep me down."

323
00:16:25.693 --> 00:16:29.530
[Blair] He just was like a Timex.
He took the licking and kept on ticking.

324
00:16:30.114 --> 00:16:31.281
[Hogan] Bang on.

325
00:16:31.365 --> 00:16:34.201
That's Terry.
That's the Hulkster. That's him.

326
00:16:35.953 --> 00:16:37.955
[intense music continues]

327
00:16:39.164 --> 00:16:41.792
[Blair] Terry's first match
was against me.

328
00:16:41.875 --> 00:16:45.879
He came out with a mask on
as the Super Destroyer.

329
00:16:46.922 --> 00:16:47.965
And he looked dorky.

330
00:16:48.048 --> 00:16:50.050
[announcer] Super Destroyer!

331
00:16:50.134 --> 00:16:51.635
[fans cheering]

332
00:16:53.429 --> 00:16:55.889
[Keith Greenberg] Terry Bollea
did not complete his training

333
00:16:55.973 --> 00:16:57.933
and immediately become Hulk Hogan.

334
00:16:58.017 --> 00:17:02.271
I mean. you have to pay your dues.
and you have to develop your persona.

335
00:17:03.897 --> 00:17:07.192
I'm a professional wrestling historian
and author.

336
00:17:07.276 --> 00:17:09.403
And despite my youthful appearance.

337
00:17:09.486 --> 00:17:13.699
I've been covering the sport of kings
for more than 40 years.

338
00:17:15.534 --> 00:17:20.581
Terry Bollea's youth and his size
made you take notice.

339
00:17:20.664 --> 00:17:22.583
He had genetic gifts.

340
00:17:23.709 --> 00:17:26.670
The Super Destroyer was masked.
and I believe that was deliberate.

341
00:17:26.754 --> 00:17:27.963
I was getting beat everywhere.

342
00:17:28.047 --> 00:17:29.923
They didn't want
people to see me getting beat.

343
00:17:30.007 --> 00:17:32.509
I had to learn how to work in the ring.

344
00:17:33.010 --> 00:17:37.848
This is someone
who had the potential to be a notable.

345
00:17:37.931 --> 00:17:40.642
But he wasn't there yet.
He was very green.

346
00:17:40.726 --> 00:17:44.188
Put the guy under a mask.
Let him make his mistakes.

347
00:17:44.271 --> 00:17:47.441
Later on.
we can make him into a real character.

348
00:17:50.319 --> 00:17:52.738
[music fades]

349
00:17:53.572 --> 00:17:56.450
["Va. pensiero" from Nabucco
by Giuseppe Verdi playing]

350
00:17:56.533 --> 00:17:57.659
Oh my God.

351
00:17:57.743 --> 00:18:00.746
Wrestling was very territorial back then.

352
00:18:01.246 --> 00:18:03.957
[Greenberg] Like the American mob.

353
00:18:04.625 --> 00:18:07.461
professional wrestling promoters
formed an organization

354
00:18:07.544 --> 00:18:12.508
that would divide
North America into territories.

355
00:18:12.591 --> 00:18:15.010
You're supposed to stay
six or seven months in each place.

356
00:18:15.094 --> 00:18:16.261
then get your bags and move.

357
00:18:17.971 --> 00:18:22.017
I was driving like 25.
26 hundred miles a week.

358
00:18:23.060 --> 00:18:26.396
["All the Way From Memphis"
by Mott the Hoople playing]

359
00:18:26.480 --> 00:18:31.568
I was finally. you know.
trading a real life for a wrestling life.

360
00:18:31.652 --> 00:18:35.489
-[engine rumbling]
-Rock and roll. Yes. sir. buddy.

361
00:18:35.572 --> 00:18:37.116
So I went up to Memphis.

362
00:18:38.117 --> 00:18:40.828
â™ª Forgot my six-string razorâ€¦ â™ª

363
00:18:40.911 --> 00:18:42.329
And I took off the mask.

364
00:18:42.412 --> 00:18:43.705
â™ª Hit the skyâ€¦ â™ª

365
00:18:43.789 --> 00:18:46.125
And changed my name to be Terry Boulder.

366
00:18:46.208 --> 00:18:49.670
â™ª Halfway to Memphis 'fore I realized â™ª

367
00:18:51.922 --> 00:18:55.300
â™ª Well. I rang the informationâ€¦ â™ª

368
00:18:55.384 --> 00:18:57.928
Gonna have to buy a ticket
to see my face. brother.

369
00:18:58.011 --> 00:19:00.347
Come in the ring.
full head of blonde hair.

370
00:19:00.430 --> 00:19:03.058
Largest arms in the world.
Largest back in the world.

371
00:19:03.142 --> 00:19:06.937
He's rock solid like a boulder.
so it's a good name.

372
00:19:07.020 --> 00:19:11.483
[announcer] That's Terry Boulder.
295 pounds. from Tampa.

373
00:19:11.567 --> 00:19:13.861
Oh. slammed by Boulder.

374
00:19:14.736 --> 00:19:18.115
[Hogan] And this Monday night in Memphis.
Daddy. when I get a hold of you.

375
00:19:18.198 --> 00:19:20.659
I'm gonna take you and bury your head
right in the mat. brother.

376
00:19:20.742 --> 00:19:22.911
I'm gonna teach you
a bit of a wrestling lesson.

377
00:19:22.995 --> 00:19:25.038
a little respect
for these good people here.

378
00:19:25.122 --> 00:19:27.708
I'm gonna put
the super southern squeeze on you. Daddy.

379
00:19:27.791 --> 00:19:31.086
"I'm Terry Boulder. and when I get
this super southern squeeze on you.

380
00:19:31.170 --> 00:19:33.505
it'll be lights out for you
and whoever's around."

381
00:19:33.589 --> 00:19:36.633
And I was talking like that.
I mean. seriously.

382
00:19:38.343 --> 00:19:40.470
Hulk Hogan didn't exist yet.

383
00:19:42.556 --> 00:19:43.390
[music fades]

384
00:19:43.473 --> 00:19:47.394
[Jimmy Hart] First time I saw Hulk.
I really wasn't in the wrestling business.

385
00:19:47.895 --> 00:19:49.771
That happened years later.

386
00:19:49.855 --> 00:19:51.190
Come on in.

387
00:19:53.025 --> 00:19:54.735
Can you believe a WWE Hall of Famer

388
00:19:54.818 --> 00:19:58.906
sitting out here waiting all day for you
to get here? This is too much. Too much!

389
00:19:58.989 --> 00:20:01.867
[announcer] Here is
"The Mouth of the South." Jimmy Hart.

390
00:20:01.950 --> 00:20:03.744
Come on. show him what it's all about.

391
00:20:03.827 --> 00:20:06.079
Show him what it's all about.
Mega-Maniacs!

392
00:20:06.163 --> 00:20:07.372
Can you believe this?

393
00:20:07.456 --> 00:20:11.501
Jimmy Hart. manager of Hulk Hogan.

394
00:20:11.585 --> 00:20:13.545
To the fans. I was Hulk's manager.

395
00:20:14.880 --> 00:20:17.341
Wrestling manager.
not real. real. real. real manager.

396
00:20:17.424 --> 00:20:19.927
You've been wearing
that outfit since 1983.

397
00:20:20.010 --> 00:20:21.261
[Hart] And I'll always wear it.

398
00:20:21.345 --> 00:20:22.804
-[host] I'm done with you.
-Done?

399
00:20:22.888 --> 00:20:24.473
-Let's talk to Hulk.
-[Hogan] Jimmy!

400
00:20:24.556 --> 00:20:26.558
-[scuffling and grunting]
-[woman] Oh my God.

401
00:20:26.642 --> 00:20:30.771
I want to talk about Jimmy Hart!
You wanna talk about and mess about?

402
00:20:30.854 --> 00:20:34.858
If it wasn't for two people in my life.
Jerry Lawler and Hulk Hogan.

403
00:20:34.942 --> 00:20:37.986
there'd be no Jimmy Hart.
Trust me on that. and I really mean that.

404
00:20:39.488 --> 00:20:42.950
I went to high school with
Jerry "The King" Lawler. back in Memphis.

405
00:20:43.033 --> 00:20:44.243
To the wrestling fans.

406
00:20:44.326 --> 00:20:47.079
there was nobody bigger
than Jerry "The King" Lawler.

407
00:20:47.162 --> 00:20:50.040
[announcer] Jerry "The King" Lawler!

408
00:20:50.832 --> 00:20:54.169
[Hart] And I remember one night.
I went by the Coliseum to see wrestling.

409
00:20:54.253 --> 00:20:56.713
Jerry Lawler goes. "Jimmy. come here."
I said. "What is it?"

410
00:20:56.797 --> 00:20:59.091
He goes. "You see that guy?"
I went. "Yeah."

411
00:20:59.174 --> 00:21:01.593
"What do you think?"
I went. "Wow. man. unbelievable."

412
00:21:01.677 --> 00:21:04.054
"What do they call him?"
He said. "Terry Boulder."

413
00:21:04.680 --> 00:21:06.890
And I went. "God. he looks great."

414
00:21:06.974 --> 00:21:08.850
He goes. "He asked me to manage him."

415
00:21:08.934 --> 00:21:11.353
I said. "You gonna do it?"
He said. "Are you kidding?"

416
00:21:11.436 --> 00:21:13.355
"This guy'll never make a dime
in this business."

417
00:21:14.314 --> 00:21:17.776
He was not very good.
[chuckling] I'll be honest with you.

418
00:21:19.569 --> 00:21:22.948
Hogan was very big. of course.
Everybody knew that.

419
00:21:23.031 --> 00:21:26.702
But not on the same level
as other wrestlers.

420
00:21:26.785 --> 00:21:29.204
[Hart] He was just kind
of getting his feet wet.

421
00:21:29.746 --> 00:21:32.249
[Hogan] I started making $800 a week.

422
00:21:32.332 --> 00:21:35.419
You needed to make at least $1.000
to buy food and gas

423
00:21:35.502 --> 00:21:37.629
and pay for hotel rooms back then.

424
00:21:37.713 --> 00:21:40.507
-[yelling]
-[Hart] Hulk learned a lot from Lawler.

425
00:21:41.216 --> 00:21:42.843
[Lawler] One thing I told him.

426
00:21:42.926 --> 00:21:46.013
"You need to take a punch.
but you don't need to take a bump."

427
00:21:46.096 --> 00:21:50.058
"You just stand there and overcome that
with your size and your strength."

428
00:21:50.142 --> 00:21:52.185
-[man 1] In the elbow!
-[man 2] Not doing much damage.

429
00:21:52.269 --> 00:21:54.980
[man 1] The amazing size
of this Terry Boulder.

430
00:21:55.063 --> 00:21:58.150
truly one of the greats
in professional wrestling.

431
00:21:58.233 --> 00:22:00.193
[Bret Hart] He was super green.

432
00:22:00.277 --> 00:22:03.697
I wrestled him in Atlanta
quite a few times in that period.

433
00:22:04.489 --> 00:22:07.993
[announcer] About to enter the ring.
Bret "The Hitman" Hart.

434
00:22:08.076 --> 00:22:09.578
["Crazy" by Casino playing]

435
00:22:09.661 --> 00:22:12.414
And the match was always
about 30 seconds long.

436
00:22:12.497 --> 00:22:15.751
[Hogan] Maybe you people don't realize
what you're looking at. Daddy.

437
00:22:16.335 --> 00:22:19.504
But you got 6'7" right here.
a mountain of a man.

438
00:22:19.588 --> 00:22:22.632
I knew more about wrestling then
than he knew in his whole life.

439
00:22:22.716 --> 00:22:24.468
[Hogan] Anybody who wants
to step in the ring.

440
00:22:24.551 --> 00:22:28.430
I have $1.000 up for anybody
who can break the golden squeeze.

441
00:22:28.513 --> 00:22:30.891
All it was was a bear hug.
That's all he could do.

442
00:22:31.475 --> 00:22:35.812
â™ª Oh. what a night it's gonna be â™ª

443
00:22:35.896 --> 00:22:39.274
[commentator 1] Look at that.
Look at that. Can you believe that?

444
00:22:39.358 --> 00:22:42.652
[commentator 2] Now with him
in the air like a piece of meat.

445
00:22:42.736 --> 00:22:45.072
and a bear hug.
I suspect we'll hear the submission.

446
00:22:45.155 --> 00:22:47.324
-[commentator 1] Yes. indeed.
-[announcer] Amazing!

447
00:22:47.407 --> 00:22:49.826
[Bret] That's all he needed to do.
It was believable enough.

448
00:22:49.910 --> 00:22:53.705
It was a sight to see a guy like that
squeeze the daylights out of you.

449
00:22:53.789 --> 00:22:56.166
and throw you down on the mat
and walk around.

450
00:22:57.459 --> 00:23:00.921
[Greenberg] He was unbeatable.
He was just so big.

451
00:23:01.004 --> 00:23:03.465
He really didn't look like a human being.

452
00:23:04.049 --> 00:23:08.220
He looked like somebody
who did step out of a comic book.

453
00:23:10.931 --> 00:23:15.352
[Hogan] At that point. all the promoters.
they said. "You're bigger than The Hulk."

454
00:23:15.435 --> 00:23:20.273
[Greenberg] A big muscular monster.
so that's a good name.

455
00:23:20.357 --> 00:23:23.068
[Hogan] And that's where
Terry "The Hulk" Boulder started.

456
00:23:23.151 --> 00:23:27.197
[commentator] Oh. there's that big leg.
Huge man.

457
00:23:27.280 --> 00:23:28.448
First thing I did was

458
00:23:28.532 --> 00:23:33.203
I did a video standing
on Jerry Jarrett's kitchen room table.

459
00:23:34.079 --> 00:23:35.497
[man] When they see this guy.

460
00:23:35.580 --> 00:23:37.541
they won't forget
that Terry Boulder is The Hulk.

461
00:23:37.624 --> 00:23:39.292
Let's take a look at it right now.

462
00:23:39.376 --> 00:23:43.630
[narrator] This man
is not a television illusion.

463
00:23:44.673 --> 00:23:48.593
He is not an artist's conception.

464
00:23:49.344 --> 00:23:53.473
He is not a figment of the imagination.

465
00:23:54.766 --> 00:23:57.060
He is real.

466
00:23:58.145 --> 00:24:00.897
He is The Hulk.

467
00:24:00.981 --> 00:24:03.150
