00:35:34.757 --> 00:35:39.470
[crowd chanting]
Hulk! Hulk! Hulk! Hulk! Hulk! Hulk!

696
00:35:41.514 --> 00:35:43.641
[Linda] The reception
was something no one had seen.

697
00:35:43.724 --> 00:35:45.434
Nobody had ever seen it.

698
00:35:45.518 --> 00:35:49.522
[commentator 1] The crowd
all for the one and only Hulk Hogan.

699
00:35:49.605 --> 00:35:54.152
It was a great moment
because the fans were writing the plot.

700
00:35:54.235 --> 00:35:55.653
There's nothing else like it.

701
00:35:55.736 --> 00:35:57.947
That's why I fell in love
with the art form.

702
00:35:58.030 --> 00:36:01.534
[Ventura] The people wanted to cheer him.
People wanted a hero.

703
00:36:01.617 --> 00:36:03.870
[Hogan] The audiences throw that vibe out.

704
00:36:03.953 --> 00:36:06.622
They'll tell you
when to be evil and aggressive.

705
00:36:06.706 --> 00:36:07.999
[commentator] Arm twist.

706
00:36:08.082 --> 00:36:09.292
[crowd] Hulk! Hulk! Hulk!

707
00:36:09.375 --> 00:36:10.751
They'll tell you when to get even.

708
00:36:10.835 --> 00:36:12.503
[crowd cheering]

709
00:36:13.087 --> 00:36:14.881
[commentator]
Now some of his own medicine.

710
00:36:14.964 --> 00:36:16.340
Tell you when to turn it up.

711
00:36:17.800 --> 00:36:22.430
[commentator] Do you see what's happening?
The Hulk is coming alive. so is the crowd.

712
00:36:22.513 --> 00:36:25.474
[Hogan] And they'll tell you
when to turn good guy.

713
00:36:27.518 --> 00:36:29.187
[commentator] And Jesse into a bear hug!

714
00:36:29.270 --> 00:36:32.064
[crowd cheering]

715
00:36:32.148 --> 00:36:35.026
[commentator] Out goes Ventura.
Hogan is right on his tail.

716
00:36:35.109 --> 00:36:37.528
This one is no contest.

717
00:36:38.905 --> 00:36:43.034
The Hulk driving his fist
to the head of Jesse "The Body" Ventura.

718
00:36:43.117 --> 00:36:45.536
Is Ventura going back to the locker room?

719
00:36:45.620 --> 00:36:47.205
It looks like he is.

720
00:36:47.288 --> 00:36:48.789
[Hogan] I became the good guy.

721
00:36:48.873 --> 00:36:51.083
Hulk Hogan!

722
00:36:51.584 --> 00:36:54.086
[commentator] His thousands
and thousands of fans are saying.

723
00:36:54.170 --> 00:36:55.296
"Hey. you're the one."

724
00:36:55.379 --> 00:36:59.842
This is the happiest day in all my life.
Once I was a sinner. and now I'm a saint.

725
00:36:59.926 --> 00:37:03.387
The reason is because of Dusty Rhodes.
Dusty Rhodes. "The American Dream."

726
00:37:03.471 --> 00:37:06.098
Dreams that you saved up for a lifetime.

727
00:37:06.182 --> 00:37:10.186
and that's things
that you couldn't reach out and get.

728
00:37:10.269 --> 00:37:12.230
"The Dream" taught me
what it was all about.

729
00:37:12.313 --> 00:37:15.650
He taught me about loving. living.
fighting. and getting down to war.

730
00:37:15.733 --> 00:37:19.153
About ten years ago.
I left Tampa. Florida. my hometown.

731
00:37:19.237 --> 00:37:21.239
with a big chip on my shoulder.

732
00:37:21.322 --> 00:37:25.368
I took on all the top contenders. Daddy.
And then the day of reckoning came.

733
00:37:27.119 --> 00:37:31.249
The only way to really grow
in the professional wrestling business

734
00:37:31.332 --> 00:37:33.793
is to make yourself bigger.

735
00:37:33.876 --> 00:37:37.797
Not just physically bigger.
but bigger as a personality.

736
00:37:37.880 --> 00:37:39.298
And that's what he did.

737
00:37:39.882 --> 00:37:41.550
Man. oh. man.
What time is it. little dude?

738
00:37:41.634 --> 00:37:43.135
What time do you have right there. man?

739
00:37:43.219 --> 00:37:44.637
-[man] Eight o'clock.
-Eight o'clock?

740
00:37:44.720 --> 00:37:47.640
I feel like I've been awake
for 40 days and 40 nights. man.

741
00:37:47.723 --> 00:37:48.849
And the reason whyâ€¦

742
00:37:48.933 --> 00:37:50.059
[Linda] He got it. you know?

743
00:37:50.142 --> 00:37:51.894
And it was crazy because I remember

744
00:37:51.978 --> 00:37:54.563
listening to him
kind of cut through a promo.

745
00:37:54.647 --> 00:37:57.650
Where does this redneck get off at?
Where does he get off at?

746
00:37:57.733 --> 00:38:00.778
He started getting creepy. and weird shit.
you know. and I'm likeâ€¦

747
00:38:00.861 --> 00:38:04.490
And for one moment. I felt a power
like I've never felt before.

748
00:38:04.573 --> 00:38:05.825
A lightning bolt hit me.

749
00:38:05.908 --> 00:38:07.326
He had a great promo.

750
00:38:07.410 --> 00:38:09.787
On a scale of one to ten.
Hulk Hogan was a ten.

751
00:38:09.870 --> 00:38:12.957
[Hogan] If your Richter scale
spins around three and four times.

752
00:38:13.040 --> 00:38:14.250
it's not an earthquake.

753
00:38:14.333 --> 00:38:18.546
It's just me pressing that big Elijah
over my head in the Sun Dome.

754
00:38:18.629 --> 00:38:21.716
[Bret] Hulk Hogan would talk
for 59 seconds exactly.

755
00:38:21.799 --> 00:38:23.759
and it was like. "Cut. that's a take."

756
00:38:23.843 --> 00:38:27.096
I don't like to overthink things.
There's nothing to think about either.

757
00:38:27.179 --> 00:38:30.182
You either can dance and play the guitar
and play the fiddle. or you can't.

758
00:38:31.726 --> 00:38:32.893
[announcer] At the age of 30.

759
00:38:32.977 --> 00:38:35.354
Hogan is one of the most colorful
good guys in the game.

760
00:38:35.438 --> 00:38:37.523
[Hogan] I figured my entrance out.
I had the music.

761
00:38:37.606 --> 00:38:42.111
I had it really. really rocking.
if you watch the old Minnesota tapes.

762
00:38:42.903 --> 00:38:45.781
But I didn't have
the most important thing.

763
00:38:46.574 --> 00:38:47.575
I needed a gimmick.

764
00:38:47.658 --> 00:38:48.868
[chuckles]

765
00:38:48.951 --> 00:38:50.745
[Linda] He was a super smart guy.

766
00:38:50.828 --> 00:38:53.748
He could figure out the big picture
more than other people could.

767
00:38:54.623 --> 00:38:56.292
His wheels were turning.

768
00:38:56.375 --> 00:38:58.961
and the character
was never not on his mind.

769
00:38:59.045 --> 00:39:03.215
[Hogan] Whether it's a big guy. fat guy.
hairy guy. bodybuilder shape. whatever.

770
00:39:03.299 --> 00:39:06.344
a great gimmick
needs to transcend the wrestler.

771
00:39:06.427 --> 00:39:09.347
And patriotism back then meant everything.

772
00:39:09.430 --> 00:39:14.727
[crowd] USA! USA! USA! USA! USA!

773
00:39:17.146 --> 00:39:19.315
[Hogan] I wasn't
into politics at the time.

774
00:39:19.398 --> 00:39:21.233
but we were in a situation

775
00:39:21.317 --> 00:39:24.487
where our country
was starting to make a comeback.

776
00:39:24.570 --> 00:39:26.155
It is time for us to realize

777
00:39:26.238 --> 00:39:31.410
that we are too great a nation
to limit ourselves to small dreams.

778
00:39:31.494 --> 00:39:35.664
Those who say that we're in a time
when there are no heroesâ€¦

779
00:39:35.748 --> 00:39:37.166
[crowd cheering]

780
00:39:37.249 --> 00:39:39.126
â€¦they just don't know where to look.

781
00:39:39.210 --> 00:39:42.755
[Linda] And the fans were so. like. "USA!"
All that "USA" and stuff.

782
00:39:42.838 --> 00:39:44.382
Of course he comes out with a flag.

783
00:39:46.842 --> 00:39:49.303
You know. it was just so pro-America

784
00:39:49.387 --> 00:39:52.807
that he couldn't even
make a mistake. honestly.

785
00:39:52.890 --> 00:39:55.935
[heroic rendition
of "My Country. 'Tis of Thee" playing]

786
00:39:56.018 --> 00:39:58.020
[crowd cheering]

787
00:39:59.438 --> 00:40:00.689
So it was all timing

788
00:40:00.773 --> 00:40:04.193
and being there with the sun.
moon. the stars. everything aligned.

789
00:40:04.276 --> 00:40:06.320
and doing everything at the right moment.

790
00:40:06.404 --> 00:40:07.488
The American reality.

791
00:40:07.571 --> 00:40:09.949
I'll tell you what it's about.
It's believing in yourself.

792
00:40:10.032 --> 00:40:12.701
I say my prayers.
I eat my vitamins every day.

793
00:40:12.785 --> 00:40:15.454
And the life I live isn't a lie.
It's what I believe in.

794
00:40:15.538 --> 00:40:17.873
And people can get off on that
because I'm for real.

795
00:40:17.957 --> 00:40:20.126
They look at me and say.
"He's not a phony."

796
00:40:20.209 --> 00:40:22.920
When I bench press 550 pounds
before your eyes. little dude.

797
00:40:23.003 --> 00:40:23.963
you say that's real.

798
00:40:24.046 --> 00:40:26.257
Everything I do is for real.
and I never tell a lie.

799
00:40:26.340 --> 00:40:29.260
[commentator] "The Incredible" Hulk Hogan.
he hears them.

800
00:40:29.343 --> 00:40:30.678
Oh. does he hear them.

801
00:40:30.761 --> 00:40:33.389
Oh. the crowd loves this man.

802
00:40:33.472 --> 00:40:34.682
[reporter] Hulk Hogan is here.

803
00:40:34.765 --> 00:40:37.268
and everything is right
with the wrestling world.

804
00:40:37.351 --> 00:40:39.061
[commentator] Ventura goes over.

805
00:40:39.770 --> 00:40:43.149
Enter Hulk. "The Incredible" Hulk.

806
00:40:43.232 --> 00:40:45.693
[crowd cheering loudly]

807
00:40:50.322 --> 00:40:53.909
[Hogan] I was becoming a huge force
in the wrestling business.

808
00:40:56.287 --> 00:40:59.999
It just so happened. during that time.
this kid came through the curtain.

809
00:41:00.082 --> 00:41:03.752
He gave me a card. says. "Call Vince."
"I'm not calling Vince. He fired me. "

810
00:41:03.836 --> 00:41:05.838
He goes. "No. Vince Jr. Call Vince Jr."

811
00:41:05.921 --> 00:41:08.674
"He's getting ready
to take over for his dad in New York."

812
00:41:08.757 --> 00:41:11.969
We're honored to have with us
the voice of professional wrestling.

813
00:41:12.052 --> 00:41:13.220
Vince McMahon.

814
00:41:13.304 --> 00:41:14.722
[Hogan] And Vince Jr. said.

815
00:41:14.805 --> 00:41:18.184
"Look. I see what you're doing
with this Hulk Hogan character."

816
00:41:18.267 --> 00:41:21.103
[commentator] Hulk Hogan.
I'd say that there has never before

817
00:41:21.187 --> 00:41:26.400
ever been any individual
in the history of professional wrestling

818
00:41:26.484 --> 00:41:32.823
that brings a crowd to their feet
with that enormous electricity.

819
00:41:32.907 --> 00:41:34.867
[Hogan] The masses and the general public

820
00:41:34.950 --> 00:41:36.911
still didn't know
anything about wrestling.

821
00:41:36.994 --> 00:41:38.996
It wasn't mainstream yet.

822
00:41:39.079 --> 00:41:40.039
And he said.

823
00:41:40.122 --> 00:41:43.250
"Look. I've got this idea
to make you the biggest star

824
00:41:43.334 --> 00:41:46.003
that this wrestling business
has ever had."

825
00:41:46.086 --> 00:41:48.422
Our main eventâ€¦

826
00:41:48.506 --> 00:41:50.591
[epic music playing]

827
00:41:55.638 --> 00:41:58.432
[Hogan] All of a sudden.
I started going. "Okay."

828
00:41:58.516 --> 00:42:01.185
you know.
"this Hulk thing is starting to work."

829
00:42:01.268 --> 00:42:03.187
[cheering]

830
00:42:06.565 --> 00:42:07.566
Hulk Hogan!

831
00:42:08.400 --> 00:42:10.069
[interviewer]
How was your ego at the time?

832
00:42:10.152 --> 00:42:11.362
Umâ€¦

833
00:42:12.696 --> 00:42:16.033
Anybody out there
who doesn't know about Hulk Hogan.

834
00:42:16.116 --> 00:42:17.952
slap yourself in the side of the head.

835
00:42:18.035 --> 00:42:22.039
Look into the camera.
there's a man talking to you.

836
00:42:23.707 --> 00:42:25.417
To be completely honest with you.

837
00:42:25.501 --> 00:42:29.338
it was way. way. way.
way bigger than it should've been.

838
00:42:29.421 --> 00:42:30.965
[Linda] Hulkamania!

839
00:42:31.048 --> 00:42:32.007
Superman!

840
00:42:32.091 --> 00:42:36.095
I just didn't realize the responsibility
that came along with it.

841
00:42:36.178 --> 00:42:37.972
[Linda] Yeah. let's party!

842
00:42:39.723 --> 00:42:41.141
He is a nightmare.

